Deconv¶

deconv¶

deconv [OPTIONS] [INPUT_PATHS]...

Options

-o, --output_path <output_path>¶
-c, --channels <channels>¶

list of channels, all channels when ommited.

-s, --slicing <slicing>¶

dataset slice (TZYX), e.g. [0:5] (first five stacks) [:,0:100] (cropping in z)

-st, --store <store>¶

Zarr store: ‘dir’, ‘ndir’, or ‘zip’

Default

dir

-z, --codec <codec>¶

compression codec: ‘zstd’, ‘blosclz’, ‘lz4’, ‘lz4hc’, ‘zlib’ or ‘snappy’

Default

zstd

-l, --clevel <clevel>¶

Compression level

Default

3

-w, --overwrite¶

to force overwrite of target

Default

False

-cs, --chunksize <chunksize>¶

Chunk size for tiled computation

Default

512

-m, --method <method>¶

Deconvolution method: for now only lr (Lucy Richardson)

Default

lr

-i, --iterations <iterations>¶

Number of deconvolution iterations. More iterations takes longer, will be sharper, but might also be potentially more noisy depending on method. The default number of iterations depends on the other parameters, in particular it depends on the choice of backprojection operator. For ‘wb’ as little as 3 iterations suffice.

-mc, --maxcorrection <maxcorrection>¶

Max correction in folds per iteration. By default there is no limit

-pw, --power <power>¶

Correction exponent, default for standard LR is 1, set to >1 for acceleration.

Default

1.0

-bs, --blindspot <blindspot>¶

Blindspot based noise reduction. Provide size of kernel to use, must be an odd number: 3(recommended), 5, 7. 0 means no blindspot.

Default

0

-bp, --backprojection <backprojection>¶

Back projection operator, can be: ‘tpsf’ (transposed PSF = classic) or ‘wb’ (Wiener-Butterworth = accelerated)

Default

tpsf

-obj, --objective <objective>¶

Microscope objective to use for computing psf, can be: nikon16x08na or olympus20x10na

Default

nikon16x08na

-dxy, --dxy <dxy>¶

Voxel size along x and y in microns

Default

0.485

-dz, --dz <dz>¶

Voxel size along z in microns

Default

1.94

-sxy, --xysize <xysize>¶

PSF size along xy in voxels

Default

31

-sz, --zsize <zsize>¶

PSF size along z in voxels

Default

31

-d, --downscalexy2 <downscalexy2>¶

Downscales along x and y for faster deconvolution (but worse quality of course)

-k, --workers <workers>¶

Number of worker threads to spawn, if -1 then num workers = num devices

Default

-1

-wkb, --workersbackend <workersbackend>¶

What backend to spawn workers with, can be ‘loky’ (multi-process) or ‘threading’ (multi-thread)

Default

threading

-d, --devices <devices>¶

Sets the CUDA devices id, e.g. 0,1,2 or ‘all’

Default

0

-ck, --check <check>¶

Checking integrity of written file.

Default

True

Arguments

INPUT_PATHS¶

Optional argument(s)
